.TH FENSTER 1 2026-04-27 "fenster @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fenster \- Chrome's on-device Gemini Nano, served as if it were OpenAI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fenster
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]
.br
.B fenster --serve
[\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB--mcp\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.br
.B fenster --chat
.br
.B fenster --version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fenster
is the cross-platform sister of
.BR apfel (1).
It wraps Chrome's Prompt API (Gemini Nano) and exposes it as an
OpenAI-compatible HTTP server on
.B localhost:11434
by default.

Two modes are the product:

.IP \(bu 4
.B UNIX tool
.RB ( fenster
.IR PROMPT )
\(em pipe-friendly, composable, JSON-capable.
.IP \(bu 4
.B OpenAI-compatible HTTP server
.RB ( fenster\ --serve )
\(em drop-in replacement for OpenAI's /v1/chat/completions endpoint.

.B fenster --chat
is a small TUI byproduct, useful for quickly testing prompts and MCP servers.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Print version and build info, then exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-serve
Run the OpenAI-compatible HTTP server (M3).
.TP
.BR \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Listen on the given port (default
.BR 11434 ).
.TP
.BR \-\-mcp " " \fIPATH\fR
Load an MCP server from the given path; tools are auto-executed in
.BR \-\-serve
mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-chat
Interactive TUI chat (M4).
.TP
.BR \-\-stream
Stream tokens to stdout.
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Emit JSON envelope output for machine consumption.
.TP
.BR \-\-system " " \fITEXT\fR
Override the default system prompt.
.TP
.BR \-\-no-system-prompt
Disable the default system prompt entirely.
.TP
.BR \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output.
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Verbose debug logging.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Generic error.
.TP
.B 2
Feature not yet implemented at this milestone.
.TP
.B 64
Invalid arguments (sysexits EX_USAGE).

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B FENSTER_BROWSER
Override Chrome auto-detection (path to chrome/chromium binary).
.TP
.B FENSTER_PROFILE
Override the dedicated profile path (default
.BR ~/.fenster/profile ).
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable ANSI colors in output.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.fenster/profile
Dedicated headless-Chrome user-data-directory (contains the Gemini Nano model).
.TP
.B ~/.fenster/extension
Bundled MV3 Chrome extension (auto-extracted from the binary).
.TP
.B ~/.fenster/logs/fenster.log
Structured logs.

.SH PLATFORMS
Desktop only: Windows 10/11, macOS 13+, Linux desktop, ChromeOS Plus.
Requires Chrome 138+, GPU with >4 GB VRAM (or 16 GB RAM CPU fallback),
and \(>= 22 GB free disk for the Gemini Nano model.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apfel (1),
.BR ollama (1)

The fenster project page:
.UR https://github.com/Arthur-Ficial/fenster
project page
.UE
